						               													<description>Saline is a game of resource management (salt) and placement (carnations).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The story :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We are in the 1770s, in the summer season in the village of Selak on the edge of the Atlantic Ocean.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The season is in full swing and you will have to work hard to become the most prestigious salt marsh worker in the kingdom.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For this, you need to create your saline (salt marsh) by buying carnations (evaporation pond) at the market and place them judiciously to achieve goals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Like a magician, the salt worker metamorphoses seawater into white gold with the complicity of the sun and the wind ... But watch out for storms that prevent production.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Manage your salt production and sell it at the right time to make a maximum of Liards (currency). Beware of the Gabelle (tax on salt) that fluctuates throughout the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Finally, play event cards to improve your strategies. Saline is a game sometimes sneaky, where all the low shots are allowed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
